# Fix: Missing 'Progress' Component Import

The [CircleVideoComposer.tsx](file:///c:/Users/elink/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/MomNest/heart-lens-studio-main/src/components/circles/CircleVideoComposer.tsx) file was using the [Progress](file:///c:/Users/elink/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/MomNest/heart-lens-studio-main/src/hooks/useCircleVideos.ts#114-118) component but it was not imported, leading to a TypeScript error: `Cannot find name 'Progress'`.

## Changes Made

### CircleVideoComposer.tsx

- Added the missing import for the [Progress](file:///c:/Users/elink/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/MomNest/heart-lens-studio-main/src/hooks/useCircleVideos.ts#114-118) component:
  ```tsx
  import { Progress } from '@/components/ui/progress';
  ```

### useCircleVideos.ts

- Added missing imports from `@tanstack/react-query`:
  ```ts
  import { useQuery, useMutation, useQueryClient } from '@tanstack/react-query';
  ```
- Fixed the `unlockVideo` mutation to use correct `coin_transaction_type` enum values (`'premium_unlock'` and `'premium_earning'`) instead of the invalid `'tip'`.

### CircleVideos.tsx

- Ensured `selectedVideo` stays in sync with refreshed video data by finding it in the `videos` array.

### CircleVideoPlayer.tsx

- Added a `useEffect` with `useRef` to detect the transition from locked to unlocked state and trigger `videoRef.current.play()` automatically.

- Verified that [Progress](file:///c:/Users/elink/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/MomNest/heart-lens-studio-main/src/hooks/useCircleVideos.ts#114-118) is correctly imported in other files using it, such as [UploadProgressOverlay.tsx](file:///c:/Users/elink/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/MomNest/heart-lens-studio-main/src/components/UploadProgressOverlay.tsx).
- Confirmed that [CircleVideoCard.tsx](file:///c:/Users/elink/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/MomNest/heart-lens-studio-main/src/components/circles/CircleVideoCard.tsx) also has the correct imports for its components (e.g., `Crown`, `Badge`, [Card](file:///c:/Users/elink/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/MomNest/heart-lens-studio-main/src/components/circles/CircleVideoCard.tsx#25-143)).
